She quietly began meeting with and evaluating Assange in 2017 inside the embassy where he had sought refuge.
Her letter noted the severe psychological toll Assange suffered in his prolonged and indefinite confinement.
Assange’s situation [inside the embassy] differs from a typical prisoner in a conventional prison,” she wrote in her letter.
Both before and since his arrest and expulsion from the embassy, Assange has been criticized and mocked for his erratic behavior.
But Crosby’s observations and statements make it clear that he has suffered severe psychological harm.